SIMPLE: corrade
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corrade
<hw>Cor*rade"</hw> <pr>(k?r-r?d")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>corradere</ets>, <ets>-rasum</ets>; <ets>cor-</ets> + <ets>
radere</ets> to rub.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To gnaw into; to wear away;
to fret; to consume.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Dr. R.
Clerke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>To erode, as the bed of a stream.
See <er>Corrosion</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corradial</ent>⟦br⟧
